news.title: Chandigarh civic body earns Rs 52 crore in property tax
news.para: A total of Rs 38.50 crore has come from commercial properties located across the city, while the remaining amount of Rs 13.50 crore from residential ones. The tax for commercial properties is higher.

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces acquires 35 acres in Pune for Rs 100 crore
news.para: A binding agreement for the outright purchase of the land in the Bhugaon micro-market of Pune was signed recently. The land parcel has a development potential of 1.3 million sq ft.

news.title: HSVP set to auction land in Gurugram to fill coffers, eyes Rs 1,000 crore
news.para: To pay the enhanced compensation, HSVP has borrowed crores from banks and it is paying around Rs 100 crore as monthly interest on the loans. Of the 96 plots in six different sectors of Gurgaon, 80 are residential.

news.title: MahaRERA tells Thane collector to attach property of defaulting builder
news.para: The recovery warrant issued by Dr Vasant Prabhu, Secretary MahaRERA last week has now sent a sense of relief among the 15 residents who had invested in the Atlantis project in Panchpakhadi area of Thane.

news.title: Kansai Nerolac Paints buys office for HQ  worth Rs 85 crore in Mumbai
news.para: The subsidiary of Japan’s Kansai Paint has bought an entire floor of office space spread over 35,000 sq ft in realty developer Marathon Group’s commercial project Marathon Futurex on Delisle Road.

news.title: Orient Cement's net profit declines 18.9% to Rs 43.7 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Orient Cement's total expenses stood at Rs 552.61 crore in the December 2021 quarter, a 4.61 per cent jump as against Rs 528.24 crore a year ago.

news.title: GIC Housing Finance's net profit rises 26% to Rs 76 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income, however, fell to Rs 293 crore in Q3 FY'22 as against Rs 312 crore in the same quarter of the previous fiscal year, GIC Housing Finance said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: DLF's net profit falls 15% to Rs 379 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income of DLF during October-December 2021 grew marginally to Rs 1,686.92 crore, compared with Rs 1,668.22 crore in the year-ago period, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: China Evergrande Group seeks legal advice over Hong Kong rural plot
news.para: The assets are charged as security for a financing transaction for $520 million advanced to the group in January 2021, Evergrande said in a filing to the Hong Kong stock exchange.

news.title: Sebi extends time period to auction properties of Kerala Housing Finance to Feb 18
news.para: In addition, the regulator has extended the last date of submission of the bids to February 15, from January 31, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) said in a notice.

news.title: Chandigarh administration launches first co-work space at IT Park
news.para: Despite the Covid pandemic and reservations about physical gatherings, 50% of the 68 seats in the Entrepreneur Development Centre (EDC) building have been occupied and booked by entrepreneurs.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad development body to meet owners of layouts on February 8
news.para: HDUDA chairman Nagesh Kalburgi said on Sunday that HDUDA had issued notices to some layout owners at Hosayellapur, Somapur Road, Govankoppa and Hosayellapur on Navalgund Road saying their layouts were unauthorised and they would be cleared.

news.title: Rajasthan mines department gets Rs 46,000 crore from limestone auctions
news.para: This is one of the highest revenues received through auctions in the country since the amendment of MMDR Act in 2015. The mineral blocks two each in Nagaur and Jhunjhunu fetched premium of 185%.

news.title: Government sets up national land monetisation corporation
news.para: CPSEs have referred 3,400 acres of land and other non-core assets for monetisation from CPSEs including MTNL, BSNL, BPCL, B&R, BEML, HMT Ltd, Instrumentation Ltd.

news.title: Construction equipment makers plan to go electric
news.para: Top names in the business like JCB, Volvo CE and Schwing Stetter are either already working on electric versions of some of their big yellow machines or conducting feasibility studies for the launch of select global e-applications in India.
